com.qtplaf.library.util

Class Timestamp

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Date
      • java.sql.Timestamp
        • com.qtplaf.library.util.Timestamp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.util.Date>

    public class Timestamp
extends java.sql.Timestamp
    A Timestamp that conforms with the contract of hash code. Note that the superclass java.sql.Timestamp does not. It's useful to have values used directly as keys in hash maps.
    Author:
    Miquel Sas
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
